HEADWORD: Mad apple
<hw>Mad" ap`ple</hw></mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The eggplant bush
(<spn>Solanum melongena</spn>). See <er>Eggplant</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> eggplant, aubergine, brinjal, eggplant bush, garden
egg, <spn>Solanum melongena</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The fruit of the eggplant bush, a large egg-shaped
vegetable having a shiny skin typically dark purple but occasionally
white or yellow.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> eggplant, aubergine.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

